WEBVTT

1
00:02:42.287 --> 00:02:43.288
I’m home.

2
00:02:44.205 --> 00:02:45.331
Hey. you’re home.

3
00:02:48.793 --> 00:02:51.045
Jae-min. your dad is home.

4
00:02:56.134 --> 00:02:58.303
Hello. Dad.

5
00:03:08.104 --> 00:03:13.776
<i>The police chief discussed
the Haeryong Auto union strike...</i>

6
00:03:28.041 --> 00:03:29.584
Why aren’t you changing?

7
00:03:44.098 --> 00:03:45.808
How about we turn this?

8
00:03:45.975 --> 00:03:47.435
This one?

9
00:03:47.685 --> 00:03:50.021
Yes. how about here?

10
00:03:50.104 --> 00:03:52.941
-Here?
-Yes.

11
00:03:53.566 --> 00:03:54.984
Is it here?

12
00:03:55.068 --> 00:03:56.736
It fits.

13
00:03:56.819 --> 00:03:57.862
Good.

14
00:04:03.785 --> 00:04:05.286
What’s with the hammer?

15
00:04:37.735 --> 00:04:39.946
<i>The doors are opening.</i>

16
00:04:46.619 --> 00:04:48.454
Come on!

17
00:04:49.163 --> 00:04:52.125
<i>Attention please.</i>

18
00:04:52.208 --> 00:04:55.420
<i>To maintain a safe distance
with the subway in front.</i>

19
00:04:55.503 --> 00:04:57.588
<i>we have stopped momentarily.</i>

20
00:04:57.672 --> 00:05:01.426
<i>We apologize for this inconvenience.</i>

21
00:05:02.135 --> 00:05:04.095
Excuse me. I’m getting off!

22
00:05:04.178 --> 00:05:05.346
Pardon me!

23
00:05:07.724 --> 00:05:08.975
One moment!

24
00:05:13.604 --> 00:05:14.814
Thank you!

25
00:05:19.610 --> 00:05:20.987
Pardon me.

26
00:05:40.673 --> 00:05:41.883
Sorry.

27
00:05:46.387 --> 00:05:48.598
I’m sorry. pardon me.

28
00:06:03.154 --> 00:06:04.697
Not again...

29
00:06:25.426 --> 00:06:28.054
<i>Office check-in complete.</i>

30
00:06:38.231 --> 00:06:40.983
Sales Team One. let’s start the meeting.

31
00:06:41.192 --> 00:06:42.985
Gather. everyone.

32
00:06:43.069 --> 00:06:44.487
Good morning.

33
00:06:45.196 --> 00:06:46.405
Good morning.

34
00:06:48.032 --> 00:06:50.368
Yes. please continue.

35
00:06:50.952 --> 00:06:55.164
I would have never guessed
from how he acted at work.

36
00:07:01.838 --> 00:07:02.922
Ms. Yeom.

37
00:07:03.631 --> 00:07:04.924
Did something happen?

38
00:07:06.175 --> 00:07:08.010
-Did you see the news?
-News?

39
00:07:08.094 --> 00:07:10.972
You know. that hammer killer?

40
00:07:11.347 --> 00:07:12.181
Yes.

41
00:07:12.265 --> 00:07:17.311
-Apparently. it’s Mr. Kim.
-What?

42
00:07:17.603 --> 00:07:19.730
The cops were here and everything.

43
00:07:30.158 --> 00:07:31.909
Are interns allowed to be late?

44
00:07:31.993 --> 00:07:33.077
I’m sorry.

45
00:07:33.161 --> 00:07:34.495
The meeting starts at ten.

46
00:07:34.871 --> 00:07:36.539
Make copies of these for the meeting.

47
00:07:36.622 --> 00:07:37.623
Yes. ma’am.

48
00:07:41.210 --> 00:07:43.838
All right. could I get your attention?

49
00:07:46.716 --> 00:07:50.094
You may have already heard about

50
00:07:50.845 --> 00:07:52.680
Byung-guk Kim's case... He’s from the station.

51
00:07:56.100 --> 00:07:57.602
homicide detective...

52
00:07:58.102 --> 00:07:59.854
What was your name?

53
00:08:00.730 --> 00:08:03.232
I would like to meet
with each and every one of you.

54
00:08:03.858 --> 00:08:06.235
For now. continue on with your day.

55
00:08:06.944 --> 00:08:08.029
All right. then.

56
00:08:10.406 --> 00:08:11.824
JI-SUN HONG

57
00:08:11.908 --> 00:08:13.075
Assistant Manager Hong?

58
00:08:15.119 --> 00:08:17.413
-Yes.
-You must be shocked.

59
00:08:20.124 --> 00:08:21.167
It’s only natural.

60
00:08:21.584 --> 00:08:24.629
People usually don’t know
about the psychopaths near them.

61
00:08:25.338 --> 00:08:26.881
They’re good at hiding their emotions.

62
00:08:27.340 --> 00:08:30.134
They’re likely to have
a friendly reputation.

63
00:08:30.218 --> 00:08:32.094
He’s not a psycho.

64
00:08:33.262 --> 00:08:34.096
What?

65
00:08:34.889 --> 00:08:38.351
Mr. Kim does not have any mental problems.

66
00:08:39.894 --> 00:08:41.896
He’s just a bit tactless...

67
00:08:42.730 --> 00:08:47.193
He and I weren’t very close.
but he wouldn’t hurt a fly.

68
00:08:48.319 --> 00:08:50.988
Whatever you think. he’s not a psycho.

69
00:08:52.073 --> 00:08:53.449
He’s just not.

70
00:08:53.783 --> 00:08:56.077
Sure. it’s hard to believe.

71
00:08:56.619 --> 00:08:57.537
I understand.

72
00:08:57.620 --> 00:08:59.997
Not "hard to believe." it’s impossible!

73
00:09:04.335 --> 00:09:06.087
You know the suspect
is still at large. right?

74
00:09:08.589 --> 00:09:10.508
Do you have evidence

75
00:09:12.343 --> 00:09:13.219
that he's the killer?

76
00:09:15.304 --> 00:09:17.265
So these came from here.

77
00:09:18.975 --> 00:09:20.726
I drink these every morning.

78
00:09:21.602 --> 00:09:24.564
Do you know how much force
is needed to crush a human skull?

79
00:09:30.111 --> 00:09:31.279
It's 23kg.

80
00:09:31.696 --> 00:09:33.906
Over 23kg of force has to be applied.

81
00:09:34.240 --> 00:09:36.117
Byung-guk Kim's wife...

82
00:09:37.159 --> 00:09:39.161
Her head was crushed into five pieces.

83
00:09:39.870 --> 00:09:44.000
His mother had a spinal fracture.
and instantly died of a heart attack.

84
00:09:45.167 --> 00:09:47.712
And his nine-year-old son's

85
00:09:48.462 --> 00:09:51.507
femoral bones and shoulders were broken
and he died of massive blood loss.

86
00:09:52.675 --> 00:09:54.760
All struck with the hammer
found on the scene.

87
00:09:54.844 --> 00:09:57.305
And Byung-guk's prints were on it.

88
00:10:01.309 --> 00:10:02.935
You don’t want to believe it. right?

89
00:10:04.478 --> 00:10:08.441
So. why did he do this?

90
00:10:10.359 --> 00:10:12.778
That's why we are here
asking you questions.

91
00:10:13.362 --> 00:10:14.322
Right.

92
00:10:14.655 --> 00:10:18.117
Has he ever behaved oddly.
or out of character?

93
00:10:19.201 --> 00:10:20.036
No.

94
00:10:20.202 --> 00:10:22.246
Has he ever told you any weird thoughts?

95
00:10:23.414 --> 00:10:24.332
Weird thoughts?

96
00:10:25.291 --> 00:10:28.669
Thoughts of depression.
or troubles at home.

97
00:10:29.045 --> 00:10:31.505
No. nothing like that.

98
00:10:32.798 --> 00:10:34.884
His son had a rare disease.

99
00:10:35.968 --> 00:10:38.304
I think it was called muscular dystrophy.

100
00:10:39.096 --> 00:10:44.393
He cares for his kid so much.
I also heard he was very nice to his wife.

101
00:10:45.978 --> 00:10:46.854
And at work?

102
00:10:46.937 --> 00:10:48.898
Good work ethics.

103
00:10:50.066 --> 00:10:51.734
he is never late.

104
00:10:52.318 --> 00:10:55.946
He’s very obedient to the authorities
and very dedicated.

105
00:10:56.697 --> 00:10:59.325
He skipped company dinners
to care for his son.

106
00:10:59.408 --> 00:11:01.327
So he always went straight home?

107
00:11:01.619 --> 00:11:02.453
Pardon?

108
00:11:02.995 --> 00:11:04.205
Well. you know.

109
00:11:04.747 --> 00:11:09.126
did it look like
he was meeting other women?

110
00:11:09.460 --> 00:11:10.461
Mr. Kim?

111
00:11:13.923 --> 00:11:15.091
Sorry.

112
00:11:15.174 --> 00:11:17.968
How long does it take for a manager
to become a director?

113
00:11:18.260 --> 00:11:21.931
Normally four years to become a candidate.

114
00:11:22.556 --> 00:11:24.475
For how long was Mr. Kim a manager?

115
00:11:24.934 --> 00:11:25.976
It has been...

116
00:11:26.268 --> 00:11:28.396
six years. I think. About six years.

117
00:11:28.771 --> 00:11:30.648
When I was hired.
he just became a manager.

118
00:11:31.148 --> 00:11:34.318
So he was pushed aside?

119
00:11:34.860 --> 00:11:39.323
Well. the company promotion
guideline isn’t very clear.

120
00:11:39.407 --> 00:11:40.574
so it got a bit delayed.

121
00:11:42.076 --> 00:11:45.121
No promotion in sight.
pressured by his juniors.

122
00:11:45.371 --> 00:11:47.665
A lot of stress. I imagine.

123
00:11:48.416 --> 00:11:49.583
Not at all.

124
00:11:50.042 --> 00:11:52.920
He wasn’t someone who was
fixated on the corporate ladder.

125
00:11:53.671 --> 00:11:56.090
And he was the number one candidate
for next year. anyway.

126
00:11:58.801 --> 00:12:02.138
You’re a candidate for
a manager spot. right?

127
00:12:03.889 --> 00:12:05.558
Fingers crossed.

128
00:12:18.946 --> 00:12:21.323
Thanks for your help.
I’ll call you if needed.

129
00:12:39.800 --> 00:12:40.926
-Mi-rae.
-Yes?

130
00:12:41.010 --> 00:12:42.845
Include this in the meeting material.

131
00:12:43.095 --> 00:12:46.223
Where is this month’s
retailer sales chart?

132
00:12:46.974 --> 00:12:47.850
Show me.

133
00:12:50.519 --> 00:12:51.353
Is she...

134
00:12:52.396 --> 00:12:53.647
not in your team?

135
00:12:54.064 --> 00:12:54.899
Who?

136
00:12:56.233 --> 00:12:57.067
No.

137
00:12:57.151 --> 00:12:59.028
She’s an intern. not a full-time.

138
00:12:59.487 --> 00:13:00.863
Sales Team Two intern?

139
00:13:01.572 --> 00:13:02.448
Yes.

140
00:13:02.948 --> 00:13:06.535
But I don’t think you need to
interview her though.

141
00:13:07.036 --> 00:13:08.621
She just recently started.

142
00:13:09.246 --> 00:13:10.164
What’s her name?

143
00:13:10.581 --> 00:13:11.707
Mi-rae Lee.

144
00:13:11.790 --> 00:13:15.544
And she didn’t know much about Mr. Kim...

145
00:13:16.170 --> 00:13:17.922
-Ms. Mi-rae Lee?
-Yes?

146
00:13:18.506 --> 00:13:20.466
If it’s okay. could we talk for a bit?

147
00:13:22.009 --> 00:13:24.011
-With me?
-Just for a moment.

148
00:13:24.094 --> 00:13:27.348
Pardon me. detective.
there’s an urgent matter.

149
00:13:27.431 --> 00:13:28.557
Mi-rae. can I talk to you?

150
00:13:41.320 --> 00:13:45.741
When they ask about Mr. Kim.
just say you don’t know.

151
00:13:46.325 --> 00:13:47.159
Pardon?

152
00:13:47.451 --> 00:13:51.247
You’re just an intern.
so mind your own business.

153
00:13:53.541 --> 00:13:56.335
People are dead. Do you understand?

154
00:13:57.836 --> 00:14:00.339
If you don’t want to be dragged around.

155
00:14:01.215 --> 00:14:02.216
do what I say.

156
00:14:03.133 --> 00:14:04.051
Got it?

157
00:14:05.219 --> 00:14:06.095
Yes.

158
00:14:07.263 --> 00:14:08.472
Also...

159
00:14:11.100 --> 00:14:12.560
that thing you saw last time...

160
00:14:14.270 --> 00:14:16.814
Don’t leak office matters to the outside.

161
00:14:19.483 --> 00:14:21.151
I’m running a bit short on time.

162
00:14:21.360 --> 00:14:23.320
could I see you now. Ms. Lee?

163
00:14:25.698 --> 00:14:26.782
Go on.

164
00:14:39.128 --> 00:14:41.297
I don’t really know.

165
00:14:41.714 --> 00:14:44.466
I haven’t worked with him much.

166
00:14:46.218 --> 00:14:48.554
Interns don’t even attend team meetings.

167
00:14:51.473 --> 00:14:53.309
Any troubles with your colleagues?

168
00:14:54.268 --> 00:14:55.185
No.

169
00:14:57.104 --> 00:15:00.441
I didn’t get the impression that
he was a popular employee.

170
00:15:02.276 --> 00:15:03.736
People didn't like him. am I right?

171
00:15:04.862 --> 00:15:06.280
You’re wrong.

172
00:15:12.828 --> 00:15:16.832
There are those kinds of people
who are hated by the entire organization.

173
00:15:18.208 --> 00:15:21.670
Tactless. inflexible.
but they work super hard.

174
00:15:22.212 --> 00:15:23.464
And also very kind.

175
00:15:24.006 --> 00:15:26.258
All organizations are the same.

176
00:15:27.509 --> 00:15:28.886
Even us police.

177
00:15:29.637 --> 00:15:32.306
There are people who only care
about their work.

178
00:15:34.558 --> 00:15:37.311
They can’t tell what the superiors want.

179
00:15:38.562 --> 00:15:40.356
maintains only his integrity.

180
00:15:41.815 --> 00:15:42.983
All by himself.

181
00:15:45.486 --> 00:15:47.071
It’s all pointless.

182
00:15:56.080 --> 00:15:59.249
Ms. Lee. you two were close. weren’t you?

183
00:16:01.335 --> 00:16:04.797
I have a meeting to prepare for.

184
00:16:04.880 --> 00:16:07.633
He’s a wanted man.

185
00:16:10.010 --> 00:16:11.804
If he calls or drops by.

186
00:16:13.472 --> 00:16:14.515
you have to call me.

187
00:16:15.766 --> 00:16:17.059
Do you understand?

188
00:16:19.770 --> 00:16:20.771
Yes.

189
00:16:35.786 --> 00:16:37.663
There’ll be a meeting here...

190
00:16:37.913 --> 00:16:39.915
You’ll have to use the conference room.

191
00:16:40.165 --> 00:16:41.625
This will take time.

192
00:17:44.813 --> 00:17:46.356
-Mi-rae?
-Yes?

193
00:17:46.732 --> 00:17:48.025
What are you doing?

194
00:17:48.150 --> 00:17:50.360
This desk was messy...

195
00:17:51.528 --> 00:17:53.655
Don’t do anything you weren’t asked to do.

196
00:18:28.148 --> 00:18:29.191
Ms. Lee!

197
00:18:29.691 --> 00:18:30.567
Yes!

198
00:18:31.110 --> 00:18:33.320
-Come to the meeting.
-What?

199
00:18:33.403 --> 00:18:35.781
You’re attending the meeting today.
Come on.

200
00:18:37.783 --> 00:18:38.742
Okay!

201
00:19:12.484 --> 00:19:14.486
BYUNG-GUK KIM

202
00:19:18.157 --> 00:19:20.576
2015 SALES STRATEGY PLAN

203
00:19:21.160 --> 00:19:22.494
Just look at it!

204
00:19:22.911 --> 00:19:28.083
How can you eat. shit.
and sleep with these results?

205
00:19:29.084 --> 00:19:30.627
-Jae-il Jung!
-Sir?

206
00:19:30.878 --> 00:19:32.462
What did you do last Sunday?

207
00:19:33.088 --> 00:19:34.882
There was a family event...

208
00:19:34.965 --> 00:19:38.177
Get your shit together.
if you have time for such things.

209
00:19:38.844 --> 00:19:40.095
Won-suk Lee!

210
00:19:40.470 --> 00:19:41.680
What did you do?

211
00:19:42.806 --> 00:19:43.932
I went to church...

212
00:19:44.141 --> 00:19:45.058
Church...

213
00:19:46.435 --> 00:19:49.771
Why the hell did you go to church?
Don't go from now on.

214
00:19:50.522 --> 00:19:52.900
Or just pray in the morning!
Does it take all day?

215
00:19:54.276 --> 00:19:57.070
Am I wrong? Am I being ridiculous?

216
00:19:58.864 --> 00:20:02.826
What’s so hard about dropping off
a few boxes at the retailers?

217
00:20:03.493 --> 00:20:05.037
I seriously can’t understand.

218
00:20:05.412 --> 00:20:08.957
Who cares what they say.
just throw the boxes over there!

219
00:20:09.458 --> 00:20:11.210
There are so few retailers here.

220
00:20:11.293 --> 00:20:14.129
and you do nothing
but fiddle with numbers...

221
00:20:14.213 --> 00:20:15.964
Is that what you call making sales?

222
00:20:16.381 --> 00:20:18.425
Talking about it pisses me off more. Ms. Hong. get up.

223
00:20:26.225 --> 00:20:28.268
Didn’t you come to work last Sunday?

224
00:20:28.602 --> 00:20:29.478
Yes.

225
00:20:29.728 --> 00:20:32.064
Your sales went up five percent. right?

226
00:20:33.023 --> 00:20:36.109
She went to one of the retailers
and wailed.

227
00:20:36.568 --> 00:20:40.155
Their boss called me.
and ordered 20 more boxes.

228
00:20:40.572 --> 00:20:43.575
Those were crocodile tears. you hear me?

229
00:20:43.951 --> 00:20:46.828
She put on a hell of a show!

230
00:20:48.538 --> 00:20:49.706
Pathetic fools.

231
00:20:54.169 --> 00:20:57.047
Who will finish the sales strategy plan
that Kim was working on?

232
00:20:58.840 --> 00:21:00.759
-Jae-il Jung.
-Yes?

233
00:21:00.842 --> 00:21:02.302
Finish it up by this week.

234
00:21:02.678 --> 00:21:03.553
Me?

235
00:21:08.100 --> 00:21:08.934
Okay.

236
00:21:09.017 --> 00:21:11.395
Don’t get disturbed
by the mood around here.

237
00:21:11.687 --> 00:21:14.439
Remember that you can
get fired before Thanksgiving.

238
00:21:15.983 --> 00:21:16.858
Got it?

239
00:21:17.192 --> 00:21:18.402
-Yes. boss.
-Yes.

240
00:21:20.904 --> 00:21:21.780
Mi-rae?

241
00:21:22.698 --> 00:21:23.532
Yes?

242
00:21:23.615 --> 00:21:25.909
Not all interns become
full-time employees. You know that. right?

243
00:21:26.535 --> 00:21:27.411
Yes.

244
00:21:27.494 --> 00:21:29.371
There will be an evaluation next week.

245
00:21:30.080 --> 00:21:33.625
Complete the new product analysis.
and sales campaign plan.

246
00:21:34.251 --> 00:21:35.252
Yes. director.

247
00:21:35.919 --> 00:21:37.087
Everyone out.

248
00:21:41.091 --> 00:21:42.509
-Jae-il.
-Yes?

249
00:21:53.729 --> 00:21:55.105
About Byung-guk...

250
00:21:55.522 --> 00:21:56.523
Yes?

251
00:21:56.732 --> 00:21:58.608
Why did he do it?

252
00:21:59.443 --> 00:22:00.736
Beats me.

253
00:22:03.864 --> 00:22:05.032
Actually...

254
00:22:05.324 --> 00:22:06.158
Yes?

255
00:22:07.284 --> 00:22:08.618
Last night...

256
00:22:12.664 --> 00:22:16.835
<i>I had a few drinks
with the regional director last night.</i>

257
00:22:17.502 --> 00:22:20.047
<i>I called for a driver. and fell asleep.</i>

258
00:22:20.547 --> 00:22:24.384
<i>and even while sleeping.
I felt something strange.</i>

259
00:23:00.087 --> 00:23:01.546
Shit. why isn’t he coming?

260
00:23:11.223 --> 00:23:13.058
Byung-guk?

261
00:23:13.517 --> 00:23:15.060
What are you doing?

262
00:23:17.854 --> 00:23:20.190
What is it?

263
00:23:20.941 --> 00:23:22.109
What?

264
00:23:37.624 --> 00:23:38.542
What?

265
00:23:39.709 --> 00:23:40.585
Damn it!

266
00:24:19.833 --> 00:24:21.459
Did you call for a driver?

267
00:24:23.211 --> 00:24:24.754
<i>It was just a dream.</i>

268
00:24:25.839 --> 00:24:27.340
It really was a dream.

269
00:24:29.718 --> 00:24:31.428
but it felt so real.

270
00:24:34.181 --> 00:24:36.683
-He’ll be caught. right?
-Of course.

271
00:24:37.142 --> 00:24:38.643
Don’t worry. sir.

272
00:24:39.102 --> 00:24:40.437
Nothing will come out of it.

273
00:24:41.313 --> 00:24:43.815
For the time being.
don’t call for drivers.

274
00:24:44.482 --> 00:24:45.734
call me instead.

275
00:24:55.327 --> 00:24:57.245
It's so annoying.

276
00:24:58.038 --> 00:24:59.873
Can he not swear?

277
00:25:02.000 --> 00:25:03.960
At least he doesn’t swear at the ladies.

278
00:25:04.377 --> 00:25:08.590
He doesn’t say it to my face.
but it’s all the same.

279
00:25:09.299 --> 00:25:11.468
I feel terrible for Manager Kim.

280
00:25:11.968 --> 00:25:14.846
With everyone there. it was too harsh.

281
00:25:15.972 --> 00:25:18.767
Mr. Kim is too good-natured.

282
00:25:19.476 --> 00:25:20.977
What else can he do?

283
00:25:22.145 --> 00:25:23.980
It’s not being good-natured.
it’s being incompetent.

284
00:25:24.522 --> 00:25:27.984
It's better to swear at his face.
Why bring up his kid?

285
00:25:28.068 --> 00:25:29.778
It’s not right to ridicule a sick kid.

286
00:25:29.861 --> 00:25:33.448
If you’re so concerned.
fetch him some lunch.

287
00:25:34.032 --> 00:25:35.992
Don’t be like that. Ms. Hong.

288
00:25:36.743 --> 00:25:39.204
Is it okay for us to leave
without telling him?

289
00:25:41.831 --> 00:25:46.211
I mentioned it to him earlier.

290
00:25:48.630 --> 00:25:49.839
Did you?

291
00:25:50.757 --> 00:25:51.925
Then you take care of him.

292
00:25:52.509 --> 00:25:54.344
Yes. Mr. Kim is quite fond of you.

293
00:25:55.845 --> 00:25:58.807
Why don’t you go and bring him. then?

294
00:26:00.350 --> 00:26:02.769
Please go ahead then.

295
00:26:02.852 --> 00:26:05.814
Tell me where and we’ll join you.

296
00:26:07.399 --> 00:26:08.650
Must I call you?

297
00:26:10.360 --> 00:26:12.904
No. I’ll give you a call.

298
00:26:19.828 --> 00:26:21.079
I’ll join you later.

299
00:26:49.524 --> 00:26:50.692
Mr. Kim.

300
00:26:53.028 --> 00:26:54.279
Yes. Mi-rae?

301
00:26:54.988 --> 00:26:58.825
Aren't you going to have lunch today?
Everyone is waiting.

302
00:27:00.869 --> 00:27:01.786
No.

303
00:27:02.370 --> 00:27:05.582
I had a big breakfast.
I don’t really feel like it.

304
00:27:06.583 --> 00:27:07.834
You go on ahead.

305
00:27:08.376 --> 00:27:10.962
Should I get you anything?

306
00:27:11.046 --> 00:27:12.422
No. there’s no need.

307
00:27:13.757 --> 00:27:16.217
Are you all right?

308
00:27:17.218 --> 00:27:19.304
You look a bit pale.

309
00:27:19.387 --> 00:27:20.388
I’m fine.

310
00:27:21.473 --> 00:27:23.183
Are you really sure?

311
00:27:26.144 --> 00:27:27.062
Okay.

312
00:27:47.123 --> 00:27:52.045
<i>Your call cannot be connected...</i>

313
00:28:10.855 --> 00:28:13.650
<i>Mi-rae! Mi-rae!</i>

314
00:28:14.401 --> 00:28:15.235
Mi-rae!

315
00:28:16.486 --> 00:28:17.695
What’re you doing?

316
00:28:18.071 --> 00:28:19.697
Did you skip lunch to sleep?

317
00:28:20.698 --> 00:28:22.325
Well. I...

318
00:28:23.368 --> 00:28:25.662
I was up late doing an analysis.

319
00:28:26.830 --> 00:28:27.789
It’s one o’clock.

320
00:28:28.873 --> 00:28:29.916
Oh my gosh.

321
00:28:32.168 --> 00:28:34.712
The Director has a guest.
bring them some tea.

322
00:28:34.921 --> 00:28:36.047
Yes. of course.

323
00:28:56.568 --> 00:28:58.570
Yes. I’m working.

324
00:28:59.320 --> 00:29:00.822
Don’t worry.

325
00:29:01.448 --> 00:29:02.782
Actually.

326
00:29:04.492 --> 00:29:07.203
I might become a full-time employee soon.

327
00:29:09.038 --> 00:29:10.707
No. it’s not that.

328
00:29:12.751 --> 00:29:14.878
I’ll call you back later. Mom.

329
00:29:15.253 --> 00:29:16.254
Bye.

330
00:29:27.307 --> 00:29:30.059
He’s still like that at this age?

331
00:29:30.143 --> 00:29:31.227
I shouldn’t say...

332
00:29:31.311 --> 00:29:32.562
It’s all right.

333
00:29:32.645 --> 00:29:36.232
When I was in grad school.
he and I drank a lot.

334
00:29:36.316 --> 00:29:37.150
Seriously?

335
00:29:37.901 --> 00:29:39.068
Sir. have some coffee.

336
00:29:39.152 --> 00:29:39.986
Thanks. Go ahead.

337
00:29:46.743 --> 00:29:48.870
Oh right. is everyone in?

338
00:29:49.245 --> 00:29:50.747
Mr. Jung isn’t in.

339
00:29:50.830 --> 00:29:51.748
Where is he?

340
00:29:52.624 --> 00:29:53.625
He went out for a moment.

341
00:29:53.917 --> 00:29:56.836
You can greet him later.
come say hello to the team.

342
00:30:01.633 --> 00:30:03.426
Attention. please.

343
00:30:04.594 --> 00:30:08.014
This is our new intern. Da-mi Shin.

344
00:30:08.473 --> 00:30:11.684
She’s starting today
to support the sales campaign.

345
00:30:12.393 --> 00:30:14.521
so Ms. Hong. teach her everything
she needs to know.

346
00:30:14.604 --> 00:30:16.356
-Okay.
-Say hello.

347
00:30:17.357 --> 00:30:19.818
Nice to meet you. my name is Da-mi Shin.

348
00:30:19.901 --> 00:30:21.110
So happy to be here.

349
00:30:21.194 --> 00:30:23.780
You graduated from Boston University?
And a master's. too?

350
00:30:24.864 --> 00:30:27.200
She’s overqualified for an intern.

351
00:30:28.076 --> 00:30:29.744
Don’t be fooled.

352
00:30:29.869 --> 00:30:32.455
Idiot. grad students are
the pitiful ones nowadays.

353
00:30:32.831 --> 00:30:35.792
They go back to school
because they can’t get a job.

354
00:30:38.503 --> 00:30:39.879
He’s right.

355
00:30:40.547 --> 00:30:42.924
I didn’t have the courage
to start working right away.

356
00:30:43.007 --> 00:30:45.009
so I dabbled in everything for a while.

357
00:30:45.426 --> 00:30:48.680
Please pass on your experience.
I’ll work really hard.

358
00:30:49.305 --> 00:30:51.766
You were abroad for so long.
how is your Korean?

359
00:30:51.850 --> 00:30:54.686
It's fine. While doing my master's.
I did some tutoring work as well.

360
00:30:54.769 --> 00:30:57.856
Then you should tutor my daughter.

361
00:30:59.440 --> 00:31:01.442
Come. let’s chat.

362
00:31:49.407 --> 00:31:50.742
You haven’t gone home yet? Not yet. good night.

363
00:31:52.243 --> 00:31:53.620
-You. too.
-Yes. sir.

364
00:32:08.468 --> 00:32:11.804
Shit. which bastard put this on my desk?

365
00:32:17.727 --> 00:32:18.728
Sweetie.

366
00:32:19.771 --> 00:32:22.398
it’s really hard to afford
a home in Seoul nowadays.

367
00:32:22.482 --> 00:32:23.608
You know that.

368
00:32:24.817 --> 00:32:25.693
Hey!

369
00:32:26.319 --> 00:32:27.737
What do you think I am?

370
00:32:29.364 --> 00:32:30.531
This is nuts.

371
00:32:30.615 --> 00:32:35.453
I’m not saying we shouldn’t get married.
let’s talk about it in a year...

372
00:32:35.536 --> 00:32:36.412
Damn.

373
00:32:36.746 --> 00:32:38.247
Stop crying!

374
00:32:44.087 --> 00:32:46.631
Can’t you understand my situation?

375
00:32:47.590 --> 00:32:49.092
I don't want to borrow money for this.

376
00:32:50.385 --> 00:32:52.053
Come on. let’s not fight.

377
00:32:53.304 --> 00:32:54.430
I’m working overtime.

378
00:32:55.974 --> 00:32:58.226
There’s a report I have to submit today. Walk home safely. Bye.

379
00:33:09.988 --> 00:33:12.156
Fuck. give me a break.

380
00:33:13.533 --> 00:33:15.243
HAMMER SLAUGHTER CASE Cheil F&amp;B Sales Manager

381
00:33:18.830 --> 00:33:19.831
Detective.

382
00:33:20.540 --> 00:33:22.250
It’s Kim’s call log for that day.

383
00:33:23.793 --> 00:33:26.879
Nothing unusual.
calls to his retail partners.

384
00:33:28.256 --> 00:33:30.842
He just worked prior to the killing spree.

385
00:33:35.471 --> 00:33:37.515
Detective! Hurry!

386
00:33:38.599 --> 00:33:41.978
It's the security camera footage of
the parking lot on the day of the murder.

387
00:33:52.822 --> 00:33:53.906
It’s Kim.

388
00:33:54.323 --> 00:33:55.950
He’s completely insane.

389
00:33:56.576 --> 00:33:59.078
Look at the time. 10:05 p.m.

390
00:33:59.579 --> 00:34:01.622
The crime was committed at 9:20 p.m.

391
00:34:02.081 --> 00:34:05.209
He slaughtered his family.
and came back to work.

392
00:34:06.294 --> 00:34:07.295
Other angles?

393
00:34:07.420 --> 00:34:10.298
None. we checked everything.

394
00:34:10.882 --> 00:34:15.720
but there are only footages of him
entering the parking lot.

395
00:34:16.262 --> 00:34:18.139
Not even an elevator feed?

396
00:34:18.473 --> 00:34:21.768
The elevator was under maintenance
since 9:00 p.m.

397
00:34:24.604 --> 00:34:26.606
So. when did he leave?

398
00:34:27.440 --> 00:34:28.483
We don’t know.

399
00:34:28.566 --> 00:34:30.193
He was never captured leaving.

400
00:34:30.610 --> 00:34:31.903
What are you saying?

401
00:34:31.986 --> 00:34:33.654
Maybe he’s still in the building.

402
00:35:34.006 --> 00:35:36.300
I’m still working! Hey!

403
00:35:38.427 --> 00:35:39.554
You can’t reach them?

404
00:35:39.887 --> 00:35:41.139
What about the maintenance office?

405
00:35:41.722 --> 00:35:43.641
Try again. and call me if you reach them.

406
00:35:43.724 --> 00:35:44.684
Okay.

407
00:36:09.083 --> 00:36:12.295
Who is it? Who’s fucking around?

408
00:36:13.462 --> 00:36:14.589
Damn it!

409
00:36:19.802 --> 00:36:21.429
This is driving me nuts! Mr. Kim?

410
00:36:40.281 --> 00:36:42.116
Jae-il. are you still working?

411
00:36:53.085 --> 00:36:55.171
Sir. why are you here?

412
00:36:58.549 --> 00:37:01.969
Come on. man. Why does anyone come here?

413
00:37:17.026 --> 00:37:18.361
Sales Strategy Plan...

414
00:37:19.528 --> 00:37:21.280
What a headache.

415
00:37:26.118 --> 00:37:27.912
Call the cops now

416
00:37:43.427 --> 00:37:44.887
You son of a bitch!

417
00:37:45.638 --> 00:37:48.975
What the hell. man. Why are you here?

418
00:37:59.068 --> 00:37:59.944
Stay back!

419
00:38:08.619 --> 00:38:09.537
Damn it!

420
00:38:35.563 --> 00:38:37.023
You’re so dead.

421
00:39:31.494 --> 00:39:34.497
-<i>Alarm has already been deactivated.</i>
-Weird. is someone here?

422
00:40:28.509 --> 00:40:29.510
The intern?

423
00:40:35.141 --> 00:40:36.809
Why are you here at this hour?

424
00:40:40.438 --> 00:40:42.398
Didn’t you check out earlier?

425
00:40:42.565 --> 00:40:43.816
Holy crap.

426
00:40:43.899 --> 00:40:46.485
Didn’t you leave at around nine?

427
00:40:47.820 --> 00:40:49.071
I came back.

428
00:40:49.488 --> 00:40:52.741
It was raining.
and I wanted to work at home.

429
00:40:53.117 --> 00:40:55.161
But I left this file here...

430
00:40:57.413 --> 00:40:58.247
Yes.

431
00:40:58.456 --> 00:41:01.167
<i>I checked the parking lot thoroughly.</i>

432
00:41:01.667 --> 00:41:03.377
<i>He wouldn’t still be here.</i>

433
00:41:03.461 --> 00:41:04.378
<i>Should I come up?</i>

434
00:41:04.670 --> 00:41:05.838
Forget it.

435
00:41:06.881 --> 00:41:08.507
You’re on security detail tonight.

436
00:41:08.591 --> 00:41:10.885
<i>What? But I have to...</i>

437
00:41:46.837 --> 00:41:50.216
You live so far away.
The commute must be hard.

438
00:41:52.092 --> 00:41:54.553
Rent in Seoul is too expensive.

439
00:41:55.471 --> 00:41:57.348
I’m used to it now.

440
00:41:57.765 --> 00:42:00.017
-Where's your hometown?
-Gwangju.

441
00:42:02.186 --> 00:42:03.395
When did you move?

442
00:42:04.063 --> 00:42:08.275
About a year ago. when I got hired.

443
00:42:10.694 --> 00:42:12.154
No southern accent though.

444
00:42:12.905 --> 00:42:14.782
I haven’t used it since junior high.

445
00:42:15.991 --> 00:42:16.825
Why?

446
00:42:18.285 --> 00:42:20.496
I wanted to work in Seoul.

447
00:42:22.748 --> 00:42:24.375
Seoul is not perfect. you know.

448
00:42:49.775 --> 00:42:52.528
Thank you for taking me home.

449
00:42:55.948 --> 00:42:56.824
You live here?

450
00:42:57.241 --> 00:42:58.075
Yes.

451
00:43:01.161 --> 00:43:02.288
You’ll be seeing me often.

452
00:43:06.333 --> 00:43:07.293
You

453
00:43:08.627 --> 00:43:10.504
were right.

454
00:43:13.257 --> 00:43:14.258
I...

455
00:43:15.426 --> 00:43:18.178
I looked up to Mr. Kim.

456
00:43:19.597 --> 00:43:25.311
Of all my seniors.
only he treated me warmly.

457
00:43:27.354 --> 00:43:31.150
Seoul is unfamiliar.
and so are the people.

458
00:43:32.901 --> 00:43:35.821
and he was so kind.
even though I was an intern.

459
00:43:38.324 --> 00:43:41.160
I don’t know what the others said.

460
00:43:42.870 --> 00:43:45.039
but to me. he was a good man.

461
00:43:51.086 --> 00:43:52.254
Go and get some rest.

462
00:44:13.275 --> 00:44:16.195
<i>I’m rechecking everything.
but he’s nowhere.</i>

463
00:44:16.278 --> 00:44:17.613
Still no footage of him leaving?

464
00:44:17.696 --> 00:44:19.490
<i>No. How should I proceed?</i>

465
00:44:21.283 --> 00:44:25.537
Just in case. check all the
security footage surrounding the building.

466
00:44:26.288 --> 00:44:27.247
Yes.

467
00:44:47.643 --> 00:44:49.103
-No one left?
-What?

468
00:44:50.312 --> 00:44:51.146
No.

469
00:44:51.230 --> 00:44:53.232
Shall I get you a blanket?

470
00:44:53.941 --> 00:44:55.109
Sorry. sir.

471
00:45:10.374 --> 00:45:12.167
-This is good...
-Thank you.

472
00:45:13.335 --> 00:45:14.169
Good morning.

473
00:45:14.253 --> 00:45:15.546
-Good morning.
-Morning. boss.

474
00:45:18.257 --> 00:45:19.091
Where’s Jae-il?

475
00:45:20.050 --> 00:45:21.718
He’s...

476
00:45:22.803 --> 00:45:24.179
not in yet. I guess.

477
00:45:27.724 --> 00:45:29.351
That idiot.

478
00:45:32.020 --> 00:45:34.064
What did the cops ask?

479
00:45:34.440 --> 00:45:37.192
They only asked standard questions.

480
00:45:38.026 --> 00:45:39.736
There’s not much info to give.

481
00:45:39.820 --> 00:45:42.573
Keep your people quiet.

482
00:45:43.157 --> 00:45:46.869
-Yes. don’t worry.
-Did he have any issues?

483
00:45:47.202 --> 00:45:48.704
It was brutal.

484
00:45:48.787 --> 00:45:50.622
It was nothing like that.

485
00:45:51.373 --> 00:45:56.086
Anyway. Cheil should never
be mentioned in the media.

486
00:46:21.487 --> 00:46:23.906
JAE-IL JUNG SALES TEAM TWO This is nuts. I want to die.

487
00:46:57.731 --> 00:47:01.652
-The ceiling couldn’t hold the weight.
-What about the neck wound?

488
00:47:01.944 --> 00:47:05.447
It happens when the rope
tightens around the neck.

489
00:47:06.240 --> 00:47:09.785
According to the coroner.
it’s a common hanging pattern.

490
00:47:34.893 --> 00:47:36.728
What about his last call?

491
00:47:37.229 --> 00:47:39.773
I verified that it was his fiancée.

492
00:47:40.649 --> 00:47:43.860
They weren’t fighting.
just a small lover's quarrel.

493
00:47:44.903 --> 00:47:45.904
I was told

494
00:47:46.446 --> 00:47:49.491
that his stock portfolio crashed
and he was upset.

495
00:47:50.075 --> 00:47:52.953
It’s Byung-guk Kim. he’s the killer!

496
00:47:53.954 --> 00:47:57.749
You cops are pathetic!
Can’t you even catch an idiot?

497
00:47:57.833 --> 00:48:01.295
Since you’re jerking off here.
everything is going to shit!

498
00:48:01.628 --> 00:48:02.462
What?

499
00:48:02.546 --> 00:48:04.840
-You piece of trash!
-Director. let’s go.

500
00:48:04.923 --> 00:48:08.760
Are you taking it easy.
since the government signs your check?

501
00:48:09.261 --> 00:48:11.138
You’re all incompetent idiots!

502
00:48:11.763 --> 00:48:15.976
-Cops should be evaluated! You hear me?
-I agree.

503
00:48:16.059 --> 00:48:18.729
Fire all the underperforming pigs!

504
00:48:18.812 --> 00:48:20.230
Son of a bitch.

505
00:48:20.314 --> 00:48:21.898
Catch that Byung-guk.

506
00:48:30.657 --> 00:48:32.159
I didn’t see Ms. Lee there.

507
00:48:34.411 --> 00:48:37.414
No need for an intern to attend a funeral.

508
00:48:38.081 --> 00:48:39.583
She’s still your teammate.

509
00:48:41.460 --> 00:48:42.502
Not yet.

510
00:48:44.630 --> 00:48:46.506
The director can really let loose.

511
00:48:48.175 --> 00:48:51.720
Claiming Byung-guk killed Jae-il.
and all that.

512
00:48:55.599 --> 00:48:57.059
I agree with him.

513
00:49:01.938 --> 00:49:02.981
Look here.

514
00:49:03.523 --> 00:49:05.275
We determine if it’s a murder or not.

515
00:49:07.986 --> 00:49:09.279
Jae-il Jung

516
00:49:10.489 --> 00:49:12.157
was killed by Byung-guk.

517
00:49:20.374 --> 00:49:23.627
What? Do you think us cops are fools?

518
00:49:24.419 --> 00:49:28.757
You said he’s not like that.
and that he wouldn’t hurt a soul.

519
00:49:29.216 --> 00:49:31.635
You said it was impossible!
Now you change your mind?

520
00:49:44.022 --> 00:49:45.482
It's because I’m scared.

521
00:49:48.944 --> 00:49:49.820
Of what?

522
00:49:51.321 --> 00:49:52.364
Mr. Kim.

523
00:49:54.032 --> 00:49:55.325
He is still in the building.

524
00:49:57.869 --> 00:49:58.912
I...

525
00:50:00.706 --> 00:50:01.915
I saw him.

526
00:50:04.126 --> 00:50:06.420
Where the heck is that file?

527
00:50:06.503 --> 00:50:08.255
BYUNG-GUK KIM

528
00:50:11.591 --> 00:50:12.634
SECOND HALF SALES STRATEGY

529
00:50:58.430 --> 00:51:00.599
Does that make sense?

530
00:51:04.519 --> 00:51:05.604
Why didn’t you report it?

531
00:51:10.442 --> 00:51:11.902
So you’re absolutely certain?

532
00:51:14.196 --> 00:51:15.572
Did you tell the others?

533
00:51:18.116 --> 00:51:19.034
Why not?

534
00:51:20.827 --> 00:51:22.204
He disappeared.

535
00:51:24.915 --> 00:51:25.874
What?

536
00:51:29.211 --> 00:51:32.756
<i>He was gone. without a trace.</i>

537
00:51:35.133 --> 00:51:36.635
<i>Like it was a dream.</i>

538
00:51:37.552 --> 00:51:40.055
No. it wasn’t a dream.

539
00:51:43.809 --> 00:51:45.018
I’m not sure.

540
00:51:47.896 --> 00:51:49.689
Maybe I hallucinated.

541
00:52:20.554 --> 00:52:21.388
What?

542
00:52:22.556 --> 00:52:24.599
Why are you alone? Where’s the task force?

543
00:52:24.724 --> 00:52:26.268
The thing is...

544
00:52:32.232 --> 00:52:34.025
-Turned down?
-Sit.

545
00:52:34.901 --> 00:52:36.111
For what reason?

546
00:52:36.444 --> 00:52:37.696
Sit down.

547
00:52:40.365 --> 00:52:42.284
Cheil filed a complaint.

548
00:52:43.076 --> 00:52:45.579
Complaint? For what?

549
00:52:45.745 --> 00:52:47.747
They’ll file a suit for work interference.

550
00:52:49.457 --> 00:52:53.003
I want to conduct a search
after everyone is gone.

551
00:52:53.086 --> 00:52:54.754
how is that work interference?

552
00:52:55.046 --> 00:52:59.968
They don’t want their company
to be associated

553
00:53:00.552 --> 00:53:04.055
with a murder case since
public image is everything.

554
00:53:04.389 --> 00:53:08.310
Is reputation more important than
their employees’ safety?

555
00:53:08.393 --> 00:53:10.729
Why are you shouting at me?

556
00:53:13.106 --> 00:53:14.024
Chief.

557
00:53:15.150 --> 00:53:16.943
Just give me one squad.

558
00:53:17.485 --> 00:53:19.863
-In two hours...
-And if nothing turns up?

559
00:53:20.822 --> 00:53:24.326
Isn’t that what we want to confirm?

560
00:53:26.912 --> 00:53:28.246
Hey. leave us.

561
00:53:35.420 --> 00:53:36.713
HAERYONG AUTO UNION LIST

562
00:53:36.796 --> 00:53:38.381
He’s near Bucheon station.

563
00:53:38.798 --> 00:53:43.678
Take the boys and get to Bucheon.
just find that union head idiot.

564
00:53:44.220 --> 00:53:45.055
Me?

565
00:53:45.138 --> 00:53:49.476
Search saunas and internet cafes
around the station. and bring him in.

566
00:53:52.062 --> 00:53:52.979
Chief...

567
00:53:53.104 --> 00:53:56.024
It’s already worked out
with the higher-ups.

568
00:53:58.193 --> 00:54:00.487
The performance review is coming up.

569
00:54:14.793 --> 00:54:16.461
BYUNG-GUK KIM LOGGED IN

570
00:54:21.549 --> 00:54:22.926
Manager Kim: Mi-rae...

571
00:54:28.306 --> 00:54:29.557
Mi-rae: Manager Kim?

572
00:54:29.641 --> 00:54:31.059
Manager Kim: Must be hard working late.

573
00:54:42.278 --> 00:54:43.571
Mi-rae: Where are you?

574
00:54:53.915 --> 00:54:55.417
Mi-rae: Is this really Mr. Kim?

575
00:54:59.212 --> 00:55:00.839
Mi-rae: Whoever you are.
stop messing around.

576
00:55:03.091 --> 00:55:04.801
Mr. Kim: Do you still
have the thing I gave you?

577
00:55:26.531 --> 00:55:27.741
Working late again?

578
00:55:31.119 --> 00:55:32.162
Yes.

579
00:55:32.579 --> 00:55:35.040
Why didn’t you go to the funeral?

580
00:55:35.582 --> 00:55:37.751
They wanted someone in the office.

581
00:55:41.629 --> 00:55:43.256
Why work so hard?

582
00:55:44.215 --> 00:55:45.383
Pace yourself.

583
00:55:46.051 --> 00:55:48.678
Head home. tomorrow is another day.

584
00:55:49.012 --> 00:55:50.138
Okay.

585
00:55:50.472 --> 00:55:51.514
Bye.

586
00:56:19.667 --> 00:56:20.919
Yes. Mom. I’m at work.

587
00:56:23.671 --> 00:56:24.964
Working overtime.

588
00:56:27.008 --> 00:56:30.887
Mom. I have to get this done today.

589
00:56:49.697 --> 00:56:51.741
MAINTENANCE ROOM

590
00:57:33.491 --> 00:57:34.701
You haven’t gone home yet?

591
00:57:39.956 --> 00:57:41.833
What brings you here?

592
00:57:42.625 --> 00:57:44.002
For my report.

593
00:57:44.627 --> 00:57:49.549
I went home to get some rest.
but I can’t focus on work there.

594
00:57:50.884 --> 00:57:52.552
You live nearby?

595
00:57:52.886 --> 00:57:53.720
Yes.

596
00:57:53.970 --> 00:57:57.599
I got a small room nearby.
my home is a bit far from here.

597
00:57:58.475 --> 00:58:01.060
I didn’t think anyone would still be here.

598
00:58:01.811 --> 00:58:03.771
Good. I didn’t want to be alone.

599
00:58:04.189 --> 00:58:05.398
Let’s work together.

600
00:58:05.857 --> 00:58:06.691
No.

601
00:58:07.817 --> 00:58:09.611
I’m actually heading out now.

602
00:59:32.610 --> 00:59:34.028
MI-RAE LEE

603
01:00:05.184 --> 01:00:07.854
NEW PRODUCT ANALYSIS REPORT

604
01:00:37.258 --> 01:00:39.886
LET’S BECOME A FIRST-RATE COMPANY

605
01:00:40.219 --> 01:00:41.220
Mi-rae.

606
01:00:41.929 --> 01:00:43.139
You’re here early. Good morning.

607
01:00:45.767 --> 01:00:46.809
You're here early.

608
01:00:47.894 --> 01:00:49.354
Did you get home okay?

609
01:00:50.355 --> 01:00:51.272
Yes.

610
01:00:59.364 --> 01:01:00.865
Da-mi. good idea.

611
01:01:00.990 --> 01:01:03.618
It’s nothing. I thought of it on the way.

612
01:01:04.744 --> 01:01:05.662
What is that?

613
01:01:05.828 --> 01:01:09.040
Hey. Da-mi prepared it on the way.

614
01:01:09.123 --> 01:01:10.208
Really?

615
01:01:10.291 --> 01:01:11.793
I’ll get a vase.

616
01:01:18.591 --> 01:01:21.094
She’s pretty sensible.

617
01:01:21.177 --> 01:01:22.053
I know. right?

618
01:01:22.303 --> 01:01:27.225
We had a chat. she’s very down to earth.

619
01:01:27.350 --> 01:01:31.062
Good education.
good attitude. and she's pretty too.

620
01:01:31.521 --> 01:01:34.357
Probably came from money.
since she studied abroad.

621
01:01:34.941 --> 01:01:36.776
She’s a rare breed.

622
01:01:36.859 --> 01:01:37.694
Right?

623
01:01:37.777 --> 01:01:40.071
-By comparison...
-Mi-rae Lee?

624
01:01:40.154 --> 01:01:41.489
-Yes.
-Damn it. Don’t talk about her.

625
01:01:43.241 --> 01:01:44.951
I wish she'd be half as good as Da-mi.

626
01:01:45.034 --> 01:01:46.786
-I know. right?
-We’re not asking a lot.

627
01:01:46.869 --> 01:01:48.287
That’s her limit.

628
01:01:48.371 --> 01:01:50.540
She was a total drag yesterday.

629
01:01:52.458 --> 01:01:54.419
She won’t make it.

630
01:01:54.502 --> 01:01:55.461
She lacks social skills.

631
01:01:55.837 --> 01:01:58.381
She’s driving me crazy.

632
01:01:58.464 --> 01:02:00.508
Always having that scared look on her.

633
01:02:00.591 --> 01:02:04.178
It kills me to even look at her face.

634
01:02:12.103 --> 01:02:13.354
I’m sorry!

635
01:02:13.479 --> 01:02:15.356
Hey! Watch it!

636
01:02:16.399 --> 01:02:17.358
I’m sorry.

637
01:02:17.859 --> 01:02:18.901
Damn it!

638
01:02:23.823 --> 01:02:25.575
HR MANAGER TAE-HYUNG KIM

639
01:02:37.170 --> 01:02:38.463
Sit.

640
01:02:41.549 --> 01:02:43.134
You requested a meeting?

641
01:02:43.509 --> 01:02:44.552
Yes.

642
01:02:49.891 --> 01:02:50.892
What for?

643
01:02:53.311 --> 01:02:54.687
About

644
01:02:56.230 --> 01:03:00.443
becoming a full-time employee
after my internship.

645
01:03:01.569 --> 01:03:05.490
When will I find out?

646
01:03:06.574 --> 01:03:09.577
How long have you worked here?

647
01:03:09.911 --> 01:03:11.913
Almost five months. EMPLOYEE PROFILE

648
01:03:17.543 --> 01:03:19.921
Why? Are you worried that
you might not get it?

649
01:03:22.548 --> 01:03:23.549
Yes.

650
01:03:23.633 --> 01:03:27.261
You have good work ethic.
and you work hard.

651
01:03:27.345 --> 01:03:29.138
you shouldn’t worry.

652
01:03:29.972 --> 01:03:33.226
I requested an evaluation
from the department head.

653
01:03:33.309 --> 01:03:34.852
Then...

654
01:03:37.021 --> 01:03:39.857
What about our new intern?

655
01:03:39.941 --> 01:03:43.194
-What was her name?
-Da-mi Shin.

656
01:03:45.613 --> 01:03:50.117
She hasn’t worked long enough
for us to evaluate her.

657
01:03:53.621 --> 01:03:54.997
Don’t worry too much.

658
01:03:55.081 --> 01:03:58.125
If we don’t hire you.
then who will we hire?

659
01:03:58.584 --> 01:03:59.418
Right?

660
01:04:41.419 --> 01:04:43.588
Mi-rae. where have you been?

661
01:04:43.838 --> 01:04:45.339
Your phone was off.

662
01:04:46.883 --> 01:04:49.093
The battery died. I’m sorry.

663
01:04:52.805 --> 01:04:55.099
I asked where you were.

664
01:04:57.476 --> 01:05:00.396
I had an errand for intern assignment.

665
01:05:00.688 --> 01:05:02.023
Intern assignment?

666
01:05:02.565 --> 01:05:04.901
Shouldn’t you do that after work hours?

667
01:05:05.735 --> 01:05:10.281
I stayed up all night
working on the sales strategy.

668
01:05:10.573 --> 01:05:15.036
But I wasted two hours
because you forgot a data point.

669
01:05:15.703 --> 01:05:18.205
I’m sorry. I’ll print it right away.

670
01:05:23.502 --> 01:05:24.545
And Mi-rae?

671
01:05:27.089 --> 01:05:28.090
Yes?

672
01:05:29.550 --> 01:05:31.636
I wasn’t going to say this.

673
01:05:32.845 --> 01:05:34.722
but why do you think
the director hired Da-mi?

674
01:05:36.349 --> 01:05:40.603
We have an intern. so why hire another?

675
01:05:42.104 --> 01:05:47.777
Interns normally go
full-time after three months.

676
01:05:48.861 --> 01:05:50.029
You didn’t know?

677
01:06:11.425 --> 01:06:12.551
Mi-rae?

678
01:06:14.178 --> 01:06:15.054
Yes?

679
01:06:15.680 --> 01:06:16.681
Crying? No.

680
01:06:23.938 --> 01:06:26.816
You try too hard. that’s your problem.

681
01:06:27.984 --> 01:06:28.859
Pardon?

682
01:06:30.069 --> 01:06:31.654
Don’t try to be so good.

683
01:06:32.405 --> 01:06:34.865
Don’t show your eagerness
to succeed too much.

684
01:06:35.533 --> 01:06:38.035
That would work against you
in the company.

685
01:06:40.121 --> 01:06:43.582
I don’t really understand.

686
01:06:44.458 --> 01:06:48.295
When we see you working so desperately.

687
01:06:49.380 --> 01:06:51.966
we wonder if it’s lack of confidence. or if you’re compensating for something.

688
01:06:56.137 --> 01:06:58.472
It feels a bit pitiful.

689
01:07:00.141 --> 01:07:04.937
So just go with the flow.
Don't always be so strict on yourself.

690
01:07:07.023 --> 01:07:11.485
You’re a kind person.
but you're a lot like Mr. Kim.

691
01:07:13.612 --> 01:07:16.240
Finish up. I’m leaving.

692
01:07:24.040 --> 01:07:25.166
Mr. Kim.

693
01:07:27.460 --> 01:07:29.420
Why do you have that?

694
01:07:30.004 --> 01:07:31.130
Do you remember?

695
01:07:31.839 --> 01:07:36.260
The affiliate who hung himself
at his own shop.

696
01:07:37.803 --> 01:07:40.056
I didn’t take his call that day.

697
01:07:42.183 --> 01:07:45.770
He begged me to save his ass.

698
01:07:47.021 --> 01:07:49.315
He sent me a package
before killing himself.

699
01:07:51.776 --> 01:07:52.985
Why

700
01:07:54.695 --> 01:07:56.363
did he send me this?

701
01:07:57.281 --> 01:07:58.532
What did he want from me?

702
01:08:00.951 --> 01:08:02.036
But the thing is.

703
01:08:03.037 --> 01:08:07.416
when I hold this. I feel calm.

704
01:08:08.959 --> 01:08:11.754
It completely vaporizes
the stress that piled up.

705
01:08:13.506 --> 01:08:14.590
This is like

706
01:08:18.094 --> 01:08:19.303
a rosary to me.

707
01:08:20.679 --> 01:08:21.847
Mr. Kim.

708
01:08:26.435 --> 01:08:27.770
Would you like to hold it?

709
01:08:29.522 --> 01:08:30.564
No.

710
01:08:31.941 --> 01:08:32.775
Just try it.

711
01:08:34.276 --> 01:08:35.319
Mi-rae.

712
01:08:36.070 --> 01:08:37.905
There are two types of people
in the world.

713
01:08:39.406 --> 01:08:40.950
We’re in the same category.

714
01:08:42.076 --> 01:08:42.910
Right.

715
01:08:43.702 --> 01:08:46.747
You should have it. you’ll need it more.

716
01:08:49.792 --> 01:08:51.627
Why are you doing this?

717
01:08:51.961 --> 01:08:52.795
Take it.

718
01:08:54.964 --> 01:08:58.259
You’re a bit weird. you know that?

719
01:08:59.510 --> 01:09:01.512
I’m serious. you’ll need it. -Take it!
-No!

720
01:09:07.810 --> 01:09:10.437
How am I like you? Why?

721
01:09:19.155 --> 01:09:20.656
I’m sorry.

722
01:09:23.159 --> 01:09:24.577
I really am.

723
01:09:36.547 --> 01:09:37.631
Ji-sun Hong.

724
01:09:39.091 --> 01:09:40.843
Is this all you can do?

725
01:09:42.011 --> 01:09:45.264
You expect me to present this
to the HQ tomorrow?

726
01:09:46.807 --> 01:09:49.059
Have you gone mad?

727
01:09:49.685 --> 01:09:51.437
Where is the data supporting
the sales plan?

728
01:09:51.854 --> 01:09:54.148
Does scribbling some words
become a sales plan?

729
01:09:54.899 --> 01:09:57.943
It’s what Mr. Kim always did.

730
01:09:58.360 --> 01:10:02.156
Ms. Hong. what have you learned from him?

731
01:10:02.698 --> 01:10:05.951
And your sales campaign
hasn’t changed at all!

732
01:10:06.327 --> 01:10:09.121
You're just proposing
to repeat last year’s plan!

733
01:10:09.622 --> 01:10:13.626
If you lack ideas.
at least put in the effort!

734
01:10:13.959 --> 01:10:16.253
It’s what Mr. Kim always did?

735
01:10:16.837 --> 01:10:18.505
Listen to yourself.

736
01:10:19.089 --> 01:10:22.301
You’re saying he did
all the work up to now.

737
01:10:23.636 --> 01:10:28.682
So you had free rides all these years?

738
01:10:29.266 --> 01:10:31.393
I’ll quit then.

739
01:10:31.894 --> 01:10:32.728
What?

740
01:10:32.978 --> 01:10:35.439
-I’ll resign.
-Ji-sun Hong!

741
01:10:35.773 --> 01:10:39.276
I feel like I'm going to die.
I can’t take it anymore!

742
01:10:39.985 --> 01:10:42.821
I feel like I’m working myself to death!

743
01:10:43.447 --> 01:10:45.574
-I’ll quit.
-Look here.

744
01:10:52.039 --> 01:10:55.501
That's right. you fired Mr. Kim that day.

745
01:10:56.418 --> 01:10:58.295
Why didn’t you tell that to the cops?

746
01:10:58.879 --> 01:10:59.713
What?

747
01:10:59.797 --> 01:11:04.343
A dismissed Cheil employee
killed his entire family!

748
01:11:04.593 --> 01:11:08.681
Unfair dismissal sent him over the edge!

749
01:11:09.890 --> 01:11:12.059
You kept quiet because you were
afraid of gossip like that.

750
01:11:12.142 --> 01:11:12.977
Enough!

751
01:11:13.227 --> 01:11:16.563
You told them it was
an ordinary day at the office.

752
01:11:17.690 --> 01:11:21.277
But you’re afraid too.

753
01:11:23.487 --> 01:11:25.114
You're afraid that it’s the truth.

754
01:11:49.013 --> 01:11:50.180
Ms. Hong!

755
01:11:51.640 --> 01:11:53.309
You shouldn’t leave like this.

756
01:11:53.392 --> 01:11:54.560
Ms. Hong.

757
01:12:00.357 --> 01:12:01.859
You didn’t know. right?

758
01:12:04.445 --> 01:12:06.071
Jae-il knew about it.

759
01:12:10.451 --> 01:12:11.785
She knew too.

760
01:12:25.591 --> 01:12:28.677
<i>Korea National Oil Corporation's
acquisition</i>

761
01:12:28.761 --> 01:12:31.930
<i>of Canadian company Harvest
with 4.5 trillion won...</i>

762
01:12:32.014 --> 01:12:33.932
Could you turn off the radio?

763
01:12:41.273 --> 01:12:44.151
So. the director

764
01:12:45.027 --> 01:12:47.029
fired Mr. Kim that day.

765
01:12:48.572 --> 01:12:49.907
Everything has gone to shit.

766
01:12:49.990 --> 01:12:51.742
How did Mi-rae find out?

767
01:12:51.825 --> 01:12:53.160
Probably overheard.

768
01:12:56.705 --> 01:12:59.708
She’s got a dark side to her.

769
01:13:00.209 --> 01:13:02.294
How could she keep it to herself?

770
01:13:03.087 --> 01:13:04.963
It’s all messed up here.

771
01:13:05.339 --> 01:13:07.341
I want to quit.

772
01:13:08.175 --> 01:13:09.259
Quit. then.

773
01:13:09.635 --> 01:13:12.679
How would I make a living?
Are you going to take care of me?

774
01:13:12.763 --> 01:13:14.306
Don’t quit. then.

775
01:13:14.390 --> 01:13:16.392
I just don’t want to come to work.

776
01:13:16.475 --> 01:13:17.684
Oh. well.

777
01:13:18.060 --> 01:13:19.895
The director asked me earlier.

778
01:13:20.729 --> 01:13:22.356
of the two. which one I would pick.

779
01:13:23.107 --> 01:13:23.941
Really?

780
01:13:24.483 --> 01:13:26.151
So. what did you say?

781
01:13:26.902 --> 01:13:27.820
You know...

782
01:13:30.614 --> 01:13:32.783
And what did he say?

783
01:13:32.866 --> 01:13:34.368
He feels the same.

784
01:13:35.327 --> 01:13:37.204
Mi-rae works really hard. but...

785
01:13:37.287 --> 01:13:39.623
That's the problem.
Working hard is all she does.

786
01:13:41.291 --> 01:13:42.459
I know. right?

787
01:13:43.377 --> 01:13:45.504
Anyway. who knows what will happen.

788
01:13:46.213 --> 01:13:47.881
Isn’t it because you find Da-mi cute?

789
01:13:48.048 --> 01:13:50.259
You're being ridiculous.

790
01:13:51.260 --> 01:13:53.554
Is it okay for us to just leave?

791
01:13:53.887 --> 01:13:54.972
Who cares?

792
01:14:19.288 --> 01:14:21.957
Are you all right?

793
01:14:26.295 --> 01:14:27.379
What do you mean?

794
01:14:28.422 --> 01:14:29.882
Well. you know.

795
01:14:31.550 --> 01:14:34.303
You and I should grab
some dinner sometime.

796
01:14:35.679 --> 01:14:36.763
Why?

797
01:14:39.933 --> 01:14:43.979
We didn't have much chance to talk.

798
01:14:51.820 --> 01:14:53.280
I’m heading out.

799
01:15:05.000 --> 01:15:07.085
Yes. Chief. I’m on my way back.

800
01:15:07.544 --> 01:15:10.672
Yes. I’ll get started on the briefing.

801
01:15:11.381 --> 01:15:12.382
Okay!

802
01:15:14.593 --> 01:15:16.136
Why were you in Bucheon?

803
01:15:18.138 --> 01:15:20.599
-To see a friend.
-A friend?

804
01:15:20.807 --> 01:15:22.893
To hide at his place?

805
01:15:24.019 --> 01:15:27.147
If that happened.
we would have been fucked.

806
01:15:28.106 --> 01:15:30.192
They always have accomplices.

807
01:15:41.620 --> 01:15:42.663
Yes. detective.

808
01:15:44.206 --> 01:15:46.583
What? Mi-rae Lee?

809
01:15:47.751 --> 01:15:49.753
No. she hasn’t left yet.

810
01:15:52.881 --> 01:15:54.091
Okay. I got it.

811
01:15:55.008 --> 01:15:57.970
I looked up to Mr. Kim.

812
01:16:00.389 --> 01:16:02.808
<i>To me. he was a good man.</i>

813
01:16:19.032 --> 01:16:23.412
NEW HIRE REQUEST
FOR INTERN DA-MI SHIN

814
01:17:54.836 --> 01:17:57.047
Yes. someone with experience.

815
01:17:57.172 --> 01:17:59.257
Someone good. okay?

816
01:18:00.217 --> 01:18:03.136
Some bitch was irritating me.
so I fired her.

817
01:18:04.513 --> 01:18:07.265
Look into it and call me back.

818
01:18:07.349 --> 01:18:08.183
All right.

819
01:18:09.059 --> 01:18:10.769
Stupid bitch.

820
01:18:11.061 --> 01:18:14.189
Does she think nothing
will get done without her?

821
01:18:15.065 --> 01:18:16.733
Fucking bitch.

822
01:18:20.987 --> 01:18:22.072
Damn it.

823
01:20:42.212 --> 01:20:45.674
TO: MI-RAE LEE

824
01:21:51.907 --> 01:21:53.116
FROM: DIRECTOR

825
01:21:55.076 --> 01:21:59.873
This regional meeting is really important.
Please come back and finish the plan.

826
01:22:21.144 --> 01:22:26.066
You know how much I trust you.
I’m sorry about earlier.

827
01:22:30.445 --> 01:22:34.115
By the way I fast-tracked
your promotion. Really!

828
01:22:44.751 --> 01:22:48.088
Sir. could you take me back?

829
01:22:48.171 --> 01:22:49.089
What?

830
01:22:49.339 --> 01:22:51.967
The traffic is just getting better.

831
01:22:52.842 --> 01:22:54.260
Just go please.

832
01:22:58.932 --> 01:23:00.058
Excuse me.

833
01:23:01.309 --> 01:23:02.352
Sir.

834
01:23:03.269 --> 01:23:05.814
Did something happen to her?

835
01:23:06.231 --> 01:23:07.816
It’s nothing. please go inside.

836
01:23:08.441 --> 01:23:09.567
Is she dead?

837
01:23:25.458 --> 01:23:26.418
<i>That night</i>

838
01:23:26.793 --> 01:23:30.547
I was drunk and went
to her room by accident.

839
01:23:31.798 --> 01:23:35.969
And she was there.
in the middle of the room.

840
01:23:36.469 --> 01:23:38.221
Standing there like a statue.

841
01:23:39.347 --> 01:23:41.182
She held a knife.

842
01:23:41.433 --> 01:23:42.392
A knife?

843
01:23:42.767 --> 01:23:46.438
She didn’t do anything.
her knife was this big.

844
01:23:47.397 --> 01:23:49.107
She just stood there.

845
01:23:49.733 --> 01:23:51.526
She didn’t even know I was inside.

846
01:23:52.193 --> 01:23:53.194
Then?

847
01:23:53.862 --> 01:23:55.488
I was scared. so I got out.

848
01:23:56.448 --> 01:24:01.494
<i>I could tell she was
like a ticking time bomb.</i>

849
01:24:02.620 --> 01:24:04.664
<i>even by just looking at her once.</i>

850
01:24:06.291 --> 01:24:08.501
<i>She looked like she was possessed.</i>

851
01:24:10.795 --> 01:24:12.422
<i>The doors are closing.</i>

852
01:24:31.316 --> 01:24:32.817
It’s occupied.

853
01:24:50.627 --> 01:24:51.878
It’s occupied!

854
01:25:37.215 --> 01:25:38.049
Oh my god!

855
01:26:52.874 --> 01:26:54.667
That’s strange.

856
01:26:55.376 --> 01:26:57.503
Where’s the rotting smell coming from?

857
01:26:57.587 --> 01:26:59.088
What’s that stench?

858
01:27:01.132 --> 01:27:01.966
Right?

859
01:27:02.926 --> 01:27:04.010
Is something inside?

860
01:27:04.802 --> 01:27:05.970
What a stench.

861
01:27:43.508 --> 01:27:44.884
Holy fuck!

862
01:29:32.075 --> 01:29:33.993
What? You found what?

863
01:29:34.077 --> 01:29:36.996
<i>We got a body! It’s Byung-guk Kim!</i>

864
01:29:37.163 --> 01:29:39.332
<i>We just found him. please come right away!</i>

865
01:29:42.668 --> 01:29:45.296
Where is it...

866
01:29:49.967 --> 01:29:50.802
Holy crap!

867
01:29:51.177 --> 01:29:53.763
I told you. not at the office!

868
01:29:53.846 --> 01:29:55.681
But it’s thrilling.

869
01:29:56.766 --> 01:29:58.017
You came back quick. honey.

870
01:29:58.142 --> 01:30:00.269
Whatever. I should’ve left my phone off.

871
01:30:00.353 --> 01:30:01.854
I know...

872
01:30:02.188 --> 01:30:05.650
He gave me a really bad look
when I was leaving.

873
01:30:05.858 --> 01:30:07.735
It's so annoying. don’t even mention it.

874
01:30:11.572 --> 01:30:13.574
I said stop.

875
01:30:48.860 --> 01:30:49.861
Mi-rae?

876
01:30:53.239 --> 01:30:56.033
Mi-rae. what are you doing?

877
01:31:05.543 --> 01:31:07.503
2015 SALES STRATEGY PLAN
SALES TEAM TWO

878
01:31:09.589 --> 01:31:11.340
Why are you working on this?

879
01:31:14.051 --> 01:31:16.220
Why. can’t I?

880
01:31:34.488 --> 01:31:37.491
Where are you going?
Aren't you going to work?

881
01:31:40.828 --> 01:31:42.538
-Why you...
-Hey!

882
01:31:50.963 --> 01:31:52.256
Are you mad?

883
01:31:52.757 --> 01:31:54.133
You’re just an intern!

884
01:31:58.346 --> 01:32:01.641
You’re finished.

885
01:32:02.099 --> 01:32:02.975
Understand?

886
01:32:36.008 --> 01:32:36.968
Mi-rae!

887
01:32:37.426 --> 01:32:38.427
Are you nuts?

888
01:32:52.608 --> 01:32:54.026
Are you okay?

889
01:32:54.777 --> 01:32:55.695
Ha-young.

890
01:32:55.820 --> 01:32:56.988
Come on. wake up!

891
01:32:57.571 --> 01:32:58.531
Shit.

892
01:32:59.573 --> 01:33:01.867
Open your eyes! Ha-young!

893
01:33:05.121 --> 01:33:06.205
Shit.

894
01:33:10.584 --> 01:33:12.169
Wake up.

895
01:33:37.486 --> 01:33:38.404
Shit.

896
01:37:12.993 --> 01:37:14.662
That bitch!

897
01:37:47.361 --> 01:37:48.779
2015 SALES STRATEGY PLAN
SALES TEAM TWO

898
01:37:51.407 --> 01:37:53.325
BY BYUNG-GUK KIM

899
01:37:53.576 --> 01:37:54.493
What?

900
01:37:54.827 --> 01:37:56.787
BY BYUNG-GUK KIM

901
01:37:57.788 --> 01:37:59.373
Give that to me.

902
01:38:06.630 --> 01:38:07.881
Don’t come any closer.

903
01:38:09.925 --> 01:38:11.218
Give it back.

904
01:38:12.303 --> 01:38:14.513
What have you been doing with Mr. Kim?

905
01:38:16.640 --> 01:38:20.311
I’m begging you. I really need that.

906
01:38:20.394 --> 01:38:21.979
Don’t come any closer!

907
01:38:23.439 --> 01:38:26.066
Hey. what did you do to Ha-young?

908
01:38:27.067 --> 01:38:28.736
Please give it back!

909
01:38:28.819 --> 01:38:30.404
What did you do to her?

910
01:38:42.958 --> 01:38:44.168
I told you not to move.

911
01:38:47.630 --> 01:38:49.173
Do you think I won’t hurt you?

912
01:38:57.598 --> 01:38:58.432
Let go!

913
01:39:01.518 --> 01:39:02.478
Let go!

914
01:39:05.981 --> 01:39:07.274
Give it to me!

915
01:39:08.651 --> 01:39:10.152
Let go.

916
01:39:12.488 --> 01:39:13.322
Let this go!

917
01:39:15.699 --> 01:39:18.118
Let go! Let go!

918
01:39:18.202 --> 01:39:19.036
Shit!

919
01:40:16.760 --> 01:40:18.303
What's wrong with you?

920
01:40:22.015 --> 01:40:23.225
It hurts...

921
01:40:24.852 --> 01:40:27.479
Tell me. what's your problem?

922
01:40:28.731 --> 01:40:30.149
It hurts so much.

923
01:40:33.986 --> 01:40:35.070
Hands up!

924
01:40:38.198 --> 01:40:39.867
She's not Mi-rae Lee.

925
01:40:40.159 --> 01:40:41.744
Hands up. asshole!

926
01:40:41.910 --> 01:40:43.829
Tell him. who are you?

927
01:40:43.912 --> 01:40:45.372
-Get off!
-Who are you?

928
01:40:46.206 --> 01:40:47.750
You’ll die.

929
01:40:49.543 --> 01:40:51.754
Tell me! Who are you?

930
01:40:59.595 --> 01:41:00.596
Get off!

931
01:41:12.691 --> 01:41:13.609
Ms. Lee?

932
01:41:13.817 --> 01:41:14.860
Mi-rae!

933
01:41:20.073 --> 01:41:21.784
<i>One of them is already dead.</i>

934
01:41:22.576 --> 01:41:25.329
She was unconscious
when she was brought in.

935
01:41:25.954 --> 01:41:28.874
The gunfire must have triggered the shock.

936
01:41:38.383 --> 01:41:40.803
Cyanide was detected in Kim’s body.

937
01:41:42.679 --> 01:41:45.307
On the day of the killings.
the elevator was being maintained.

938
01:41:45.432 --> 01:41:48.185
He must have snuck in
while the engineer was away.

939
01:41:50.521 --> 01:41:52.481
This was inside Kim’s bag.

940
01:41:53.315 --> 01:41:54.441
It’s his journal.

941
01:41:57.277 --> 01:41:58.862
<i>What was Won-suk Lee’s motive?</i>

942
01:41:58.946 --> 01:42:00.572
It’s still not...

943
01:42:00.656 --> 01:42:02.574
<i>How could you not have it yet?</i>

944
01:42:02.825 --> 01:42:06.662
<i>See if he had
a history of mental problems.</i>

945
01:42:07.037 --> 01:42:11.041
<i>If there isn’t a motive.
come up with a believable one.</i>

946
01:42:11.458 --> 01:42:14.336
<i>Make sure they don’t bring up
excessive defense.</i>

947
01:42:14.795 --> 01:42:16.296
<i>You understand?</i>

948
01:42:18.173 --> 01:42:19.800
<i>Is there a problem?</i>

949
01:42:19.883 --> 01:42:21.176
No. sir.

950
01:42:21.260 --> 01:42:23.011
I’ll debrief when I get back.

951
01:42:24.096 --> 01:42:24.972
Yes. sir.

952
01:42:40.571 --> 01:42:42.573
Manager Byung-guk Kim
Sales Team Two

953
01:42:49.121 --> 01:42:51.039
The office is filled with wolves.

954
01:42:51.123 --> 01:42:54.001
waiting to rip each other into pieces.

955
01:43:20.360 --> 01:43:21.695
Have you been well?

956
01:43:24.656 --> 01:43:26.325
I heard you're getting discharged
in two days.

957
01:43:26.867 --> 01:43:27.701
Yes.

958
01:43:30.162 --> 01:43:31.246
You look good.

959
01:43:32.581 --> 01:43:33.790
You too.

960
01:43:44.301 --> 01:43:45.135
I...

961
01:43:47.554 --> 01:43:48.889
I have a question.

962
01:43:52.684 --> 01:43:53.810
EVIDENCE

963
01:43:55.270 --> 01:43:56.355
This knife...

964
01:43:57.105 --> 01:43:58.690
Have you seen it before?

965
01:44:05.781 --> 01:44:06.615
Yes.

966
01:44:07.491 --> 01:44:08.575
Where?

967
01:44:10.327 --> 01:44:13.872
I had it with me.

968
01:44:16.333 --> 01:44:17.417
What for?

969
01:44:18.335 --> 01:44:19.503
I don’t know.

970
01:44:21.004 --> 01:44:23.590
To me. it’s...

971
01:44:26.176 --> 01:44:27.636
like a rosary.

972
01:44:30.013 --> 01:44:30.931
A rosary?

973
01:44:32.557 --> 01:44:36.812
I felt like I was at peace.

974
01:44:41.108 --> 01:44:43.527
I heard you’re getting promoted.

975
01:44:49.700 --> 01:44:50.784
Congratulations.

976
01:45:28.822 --> 01:45:29.781
Hello?

977
01:45:29.865 --> 01:45:32.701
<i>This is Hanwol F&amp;B’s HR department.</i>

978
01:45:32.826 --> 01:45:35.037
<i>Didn’t you submit a job application?</i>

979
01:45:35.162 --> 01:45:35.996
Yes.

980
01:45:36.079 --> 01:45:39.124
<i>Your interview is at three o'clock
next Saturday.</i>

981
01:45:39.207 --> 01:45:42.335
<i>Please come to the fifth floor.</i>

982
01:45:42.544 --> 01:45:44.046
Okay. thank you.
